Package org.threadly.concurrent.wrapper

Class PrioritySchedulerDefaultPriorityWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.threadly.concurrent.wrapper.priority.DefaultPriorityWrapper
      • org.threadly.concurrent.wrapper.PrioritySchedulerDefaultPriorityWrapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.concurrent.Executor, PrioritySchedulerService, SchedulerService, SubmitterExecutor, SubmitterScheduler
    @Deprecated
public class PrioritySchedulerDefaultPriorityWrapper
extends DefaultPriorityWrapper
    Deprecated.
    Moved to DefaultPriorityWrapper
    Class to wrap any implementation of PrioritySchedulerService. The purpose of wrapping like this would be to change the default priority from the wrapped instance. That way this could be passed into other parts of code and although use the same thread pool, have different default priorities. (this could be particularly useful when used in combination with KeyDistributedExecutor, or KeyDistributedScheduler.
    Since:
    4.6.0 (since 1.0.0 as org.threadly.concurrent.PrioritySchedulerWrapper)
